<!-- ==================== 1. OVERVIEW ==================== -->
<h2>1. Platform Overview</h2>

<p><b>LinkedEye</b> is FinSpot Technology Solutions' shared ITSM/Monitoring platform deployed on AWS. It serves <b>16 enterprise clients</b> with dedicated Kubernetes namespaces, on-premise hybrid worker nodes, and centralized management tools.</p>

<h3>Key Features</h3>
<ul>
  <li><b>EKS Hybrid Nodes</b> &mdash; AWS-managed control plane, on-prem workers per client site</li>
  <li><b>Multi-tenant isolation</b> &mdash; NetworkPolicy + RBAC + ResourceQuota per namespace</li>
  <li><b>Zero VPN required</b> &mdash; Hybrid nodes connect via public EKS API (HTTPS 443 outbound only)</li>
  <li><b>GitOps CI/CD</b> &mdash; Jenkins + Harbor + ArgoCD pipeline</li>
  <li><b>Centralized SSO</b> &mdash; Keycloak for all tools authentication</li>
  <li><b>Secret management</b> &mdash; HashiCorp Vault with per-client paths</li>
  <li><b>HA architecture</b> &mdash; Dual NAT GW, 2 AZs, 2 nodes per client</li>
  <li><b>TLS everywhere</b> &mdash; ALB with ACM wildcard cert + external domain certs</li>
</ul>

