<!-- ==================== 4. CONNECTIVITY ==================== -->
<h2>4. Connectivity Flow (End-to-End)</h2>

<h3>Flow 1: User Accessing Client ITSM Portal</h3>
<pre>
User Browser
  |  https://indmoney-prod-le.finspot.in
  v
[DNS: *.finspot.in CNAME] --&gt; linkedeye-tools-alb-922526253.ap-south-1.elb.amazonaws.com
  |
  v
[ALB - HTTPS :443]
  | TLS termination (ACM cert)
  | Host-header match: indmoney-prod-le.finspot.in
  | Rule Priority 10 --&gt; Forward to TG: linkedeye-tg-client-itsm
  v
[EC2-B :80] (15.206.80.24)
  | ITSM Docker container serves request
  | Client identified by hostname header
  v
[Response returned to user via ALB]
</pre>

<h3>Flow 2: CI/CD Pipeline</h3>
<pre>
Developer --&gt; git push --&gt; GitHub Webhook
  |
  v
[ALB :443] --&gt; Host: le.jenkins.finspot.in --&gt; EC2-A Jenkins :8080
  |
  v
Jenkins Pipeline:
  1. git checkout
  2. docker build
  3. docker run tests
  4. docker push to Harbor (le.harbor.finspot.in)
  |
  v
ArgoCD (le.argocd.finspot.in)
  | Detects new image tag in Git manifests
  | Syncs to target namespace
  v
EKS API --&gt; kubectl apply to le-{client}-prod namespace
  |
  v
Hybrid Worker Node (on-prem at client site)
  | kubelet pulls image, Pod starts
</pre>

<h3>Flow 3: Hybrid Node Communication</h3>
<pre>
On-Prem Worker Node (Client Site)
  |
  | ALL TRAFFIC IS OUTBOUND (no inbound ports needed)
  |
  +---&gt; HTTPS 443 --&gt; EKS API Server (kubelet heartbeat, pod specs)
  +---&gt; HTTPS 443 --&gt; ECR / Harbor (container image pulls)
  +---&gt; HTTPS 443 --&gt; SSM Service (management channel)
  +---&gt; HTTPS 443 --&gt; STS (IAM credential refresh)
</pre>

