<h3>Per-Namespace Isolation (5 Layers)</h3>
<table>
  <tr><th>Layer</th><th>Resource</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>1</td><td>NetworkPolicy</td><td>Only allows ingress from own namespace + le-monitoring. Prevents cross-client traffic.</td></tr>
  <tr><td>2</td><td>ResourceQuota</td><td>Hard limits: 4 CPU / 8Gi / 20 pods per prod namespace</td></tr>
  <tr><td>3</td><td>LimitRange</td><td>Default container limits: 500m CPU, 512Mi memory</td></tr>
  <tr><td>4</td><td>RBAC RoleBindings</td><td>le-client-admin (ops) + le-argocd-deployer (GitOps)</td></tr>
  <tr><td>5</td><td>Node Affinity + Taints</td><td>Pods only schedule on client's on-prem hybrid nodes</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ==================== 7. HYBRID NODES ==================== -->
<h2>7. Hybrid Node Registration</h2>

<div class="info"><b>How it works:</b> EKS Hybrid Nodes let on-premise servers join the EKS cluster as worker nodes. Control plane stays in AWS, workers run at client sites. Communication is HTTPS 443 outbound only &mdash; <b>no VPN required</b>.</div>

<h3>Registration Steps</h3>
<ol>
  <li><b>Admin creates SSM Hybrid Activation:</b> <code>aws ssm create-activation --iam-role linkedeye-hybrid-node-role</code></li>
  <li><b>Install SSM Agent on on-prem server:</b> <code>sudo amazon-ssm-agent -register -id ACTIVATION_ID -code ACTIVATION_CODE -region ap-south-1</code></li>
  <li><b>Install nodeadm &amp; bootstrap:</b> Create <code>/etc/eks/nodeadm-config.yaml</code> with cluster config, then <code>sudo nodeadm init</code></li>
  <li><b>Label &amp; taint:</b> <code>kubectl label node mi-0xxx client=indmoney</code> + <code>kubectl taint node mi-0xxx client=indmoney:NoSchedule</code></li>
</ol>

<h3>Firewall Rules (Per Client Site)</h3>
<div class="warn"><b>Share with each client's network team.</b> Only OUTBOUND rules needed. NO INBOUND ports required.</div>
<table>
  <tr><th>Direction</th><th>Protocol</th><th>Port</th><th>Destination</th><th>Purpose</th></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>*.eks.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>EKS API Server</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>ssm.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>SSM Registration</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>ssmmessages.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>SSM Messages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>ec2messages.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>EC2 Messages</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>ecr.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>Container Registry</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>sts.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>IAM Token Refresh</td></tr>
  <tr><td>Outbound</td><td>TCP</td><td>443</td><td>s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com</td><td>S3 (ECR layers)</td></tr>
</table>

<!-- ==================== 8. ALB ==================== -->
<h2>8. ALB Host-Based Routing</h2>

